   Who Can Subit A Waiver?

   All Department of Transportation (DOT) employees, DOT organizations,
   and other non-DOT customers of TASC represented by a DOT employee, may
   submit a request to waive an internal TASC rule.

                        group of many people standing

   How To Request A Waiver

   If you have an idea you would like to try out, and a waiver to an
   internal TASC rule, regulation, policy, procedure, process, etc. is
   needed in order to implement your idea, you will want to follow these
   two basic steps:

   Step 1: Consult with the process owner and jointly develop a way to
   assess  the  effectiveness of your requested waiver.

   (Click here for more information about Step 1)

   Step 2:  Complete and submit Waiver Request Form DOT 1001 to the
   process owner and at the same time, send a copy of the form to the
   independent official

   (Click here for more information about Step 2)

